Building the dataset with Spotipy¶

In [0]:
cid ="38074e04633e47a9a4cf142bf1e19e21" 
secret = "67e54c3e15964fffb4902f0b4a9b260e"

image_size = (256, 256, 3)
queryloop = 19
client_credentials_manager = SpotifyClientCredentials(client_id=cid, client_secret=secret) 
spotify = spotipy.Spotify(client_credentials_manager=client_credentials_manager)

genres = ["rock", "rap", "classical"]
artists = []
for i in range(len(genres)):
  for k in range(queryloop):
    myoffset = 50*k;
    results = spotify.search(q='genre:' + genres[i],offset=myoffset, type='artist', limit=50)
    items = results['artists']['items']
    for j in range(len(items)):
      artists.append(items[j])

x_data = []
y_data = []
for i in range(len(artists)):
  results = spotify.search(q="artist:" + artists[i]['name'], type='album')
  items = results['albums']['items']
  for j in range(len(items)):
    for k in range(len(genres)):
      if genres[k] in artists[i]['genres']:
        album = items[j]
        if len(album['images']) > 0:
          first_album_url = album['images'][0]['url']
          with urllib.request.urlopen(first_album_url) as url:
            img = image.load_img(BytesIO(url.read()),  target_size=image_size)
            img = image.img_to_array(img)
            img = img/255
            x_data.append(img)
            y_data.append(k)

x = np.array(x_data)
y = np.array(y_data)
In [0]:
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, random_state=42, test_size=0.1)
y_train = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_train, len(genres))
y_test = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_test, len(genres))

Model 1: Kernal size of (5, 5) and pool size of (2, 2)¶

In [0]:
kernel_size = (5, 5)
pool_size = (2, 2)

model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=kernel_size, activation="relu", input_shape=image_size))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=pool_size))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=kernel_size, activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=pool_size))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=kernel_size, activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=pool_size))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=kernel_size, activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=pool_size))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(len(genres), activation='sigmoid'))

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=5, verbose=1, mode='auto')
model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=50, validation_data=(x_test, y_test),callbacks=[monitor], batch_size=64)

To Load the: dataset, model, and model weights from drive. And run the precision statistics.¶

from numpy import load
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
from tensorflow.keras.models import model_from_json
import os

# SELECT GENRES ON LOAD
#genres = ["hip hop", "pop", "edm"]               
genres = ["rock", "rap", "classical"]
image_size = (256, 256, 3)
x = load('base3B_x.npy')                                # CHANGE ON LOAD
y = load('base3B_y.npy')                                # CHANGE ON LOAD

x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, random_state=42, test_size=0.1)
y_train = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_train, len(genres))
y_test = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_test, len(genres))

# load json and create model
json_file = open('model_base3B.json', 'r')               # CHANGE ON LOAD
loaded_model_json = json_file.read()
json_file.close()
loaded_model = model_from_json(loaded_model_json)
# load weights into new model
loaded_model.load_weights("model_base3B.h5")             # CHANGE ON LOAD
print("Loaded model from drive")

pred = loaded_model.predict(x_test)
pred = np.argmax(pred,axis=1)
y_true= np.argmax(y_test,axis=1) 

score = metrics.precision_score(y_true, pred, average= "weighted")
print("Precision score: {}".format(score))
score = metrics.recall_score(y_true, pred, average= "weighted")
print("Recall score: {}".format(score))
score = metrics.f1_score(y_true, pred, average= "weighted")
print("F1 score: {}".format(score))
print(metrics.classification_report(y_true, pred))
